Description: Do not create /run/nologin
 systemd in trusty is not responsible for handling startup/shutdown scenarios.
 With that, it should not interfere with pam_nologin and should not touch
 /run/nologin.
Author: Thomas Vo√ü
Bug-Ubuntu: https://bugs.launchpad.net/bugs/1660573

--- a/tmpfiles.d/systemd.conf
+++ b/tmpfiles.d/systemd.conf
@@ -20,5 +20,3 @@
 d /run/systemd/sessions 0755 root root -
 d /run/systemd/users 0755 root root -
 d /run/systemd/shutdown 0755 root root -
-
-F /run/nologin 0644 - - - "System is booting up."
